        "title": "Doctor: expose device pairing findings",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- expose existing device-pairing Doctor diagnostics as structured `core/doctor/device-pairing` findings\n- keep the structured lint check default-disabled, so broad `doctor --lint` behavior is unchanged unless operators use `--all` or explicit `--only`\n- keep real device-pairing behavior in the legacy Doctor note path; the structured detector is read-only and does not probe the Gateway in lint mode\n\n## Public contract\n\nNo public SDK, plugin manifest, config schema, CLI flag, or persisted data-model contract changes.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/commands/doctor-device-pairing.test.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts --reporter=verbose` (63 tests across 2 shards)\n- `PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/commands/doctor-device-pairing.ts src/commands/doctor-device-pairing.test.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts`\n- `PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/commands/doctor-device-pairing.ts src/commands/doctor-device-pairing.test.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts`\n- `PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false pnpm plugin-sdk:surface:check`\n- `PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false pnpm plugin-sdk:check-exports`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed:\nExpose the existing device-pairing Doctor diagnostics through explicit structured lint selection without changing broad `doctor --lint` defaults or probing Gateway from lint.\n\nReal environment tested:\nUbuntu 24.04 WSL root, source checkout at `eff0d3cdae1ddab01f5daf7546c245f78a2ebd91`, isolated temp `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH` and `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR`, no live Gateway service required for the quiet-path lint proof.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n1. `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=<temp>/openclaw.json OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=<temp>/state PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false pnpm openclaw doctor --lint --json --only core/doctor/device-pairing`\n2. `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=<temp>/openclaw.json OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=<temp>/state PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false pnpm openclaw doctor --lint --json`\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"onlyExit\": 0,\n  \"onlyChecksRun\": 1,\n  \"onlyChecksSkipped\": 35,\n  \"onlyDeviceFindings\": 0,\n  \"defaultExit\": 1,\n  \"defaultDeviceFindings\": 0\n}\n```\n\nObserved result after fix:\nExplicit `--only core/doctor/device-pairing` runs the new structured check and exits cleanly against isolated quiet state. Broad default lint still emits no `core/doctor/device-pairing` findings, preserving the default-disabled contract.\n\nWhat was not tested:\nNo live Gateway pairing service was exercised in this refresh; existing focused tests cover pending scope upgrades, corrupt local pairing state, stale cached device tokens, sanitization, and structured conversion.\n",
